appInfo.shortDescription: The best workout tracker for your gym sessions.

help.title: What's this?
help.warmUp: A warm-up set is a light set of an exercise that you perform before the actual working sets. Its purpose is to prepare your muscles for the upcoming heavy work.
help.normal: A normal set is a regular set of an exercise, where you perform a certain amount of reps with a certain weight.
help.drop: A drop set is a set where you drop the weight after reaching failure and continue to perform reps with the lower weight.
help.failure: A failure set is a set where you perform reps until you reach technical failure.
help.failureStripping: A failure set with stripping is a kind of failure set that starts immediately after the previous set (without resting), in which you perform reps until you reach technical failure.

description.title: What is RPE?
description.text: Rate of Perceived Exertion (RPE) is a subjective measure of how hard an exercise feels to you. It's a scale from 1 to 10, where 1 is very light effort and 10 is maximum effort.

level1.title: RPE 1
level1.text: Very light effort. It doesn't even feel like you're working out.

level2.title: RPE 2
level2.text: Light effort. You can easily maintain a conversation.

level3.title: RPE 3
level3.text: Moderate effort. You can maintain a conversation.

level4.title: RPE 4
level4.text: Moderate effort. You can maintain a conversation, but it's a bit harder.

level5.title: RPE 5
level5.text: Moderate to hard effort. You can maintain a conversation, but it's hard.

level6.title: RPE 6
level6.text: Moderate to hard effort. You can barely maintain a conversation, and you're breathing heavily.

level7.title: RPE 7
level7.text: Hard effort. You can't maintain a conversation, and you're breathing heavily.

level8.title: RPE 8
level8.text: Hard effort. You can speak only a sentence at a time.

level9.title: RPE 9
level9.text: Very hard effort. You're almost out of breath, and you can only speak a few word at a time.

level10.title: RPE 10
level10.text: Maximum effort. You can't speak at all and you're out of breath.
